<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Tightens Ban on Export of Hazardous Waste </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, November 10 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission
tightened its prohibition to export hazardous waste to
non-Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development
countries.
</P>
<P>
The commission, the executive body of the 15-nation European
Union, tightened the export ban by adopting a regulation that
clarifies the scope of the prohibition of waste exports from OECD
countries to non-OECD countries.
</P>
<P>
The regulation will then transpose into the European Union law
the lists of both hazardous and non-hazardous wastes.
</P>
<P>
The commission said that the export ban should also cover the
wastes that are on the EU's hazardous waste list for presenting a
risk for the environment even though they are not on the ban list
of the Basel Convention.
</P>
<P>
The commission also said that it foresees the possibility of
further tightening the EU scope of export ban which may in the end
become stricter than the requirement of the Basel Convention.
</P>
<P>
The convention concerns the control of transboundary movements
of hazardous wastes and their disposal and is concerned with the
environmentally sound management of hazardous waste.
</P>
<P>
The EU is a party to the convention, as are all the EU member
states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
