<HEADLINE> UK Doctor Sent for Trial on Murder Charge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 10 (Xinhua) -- A British doctor was sent for
trial on Tuesday accused of murdering an 81-year-old patient and
forging her will.
</P>
<P>
Harold Shipman, 52, has been charged with murder Kathleen
Grundy and attempted deception to try to inherit her 300,000-pound
(498,100 US dollars) estate. He has been charged with murdering
three other women, all were his patients.
</P>
<P>
Police began investigating Shipman when Grundy's daughter
contacted them after discovering her mother's will had apparently
been changed two weeks before her death to make Shipman the sole
beneficiary.
</P>
<P>
A court near Manchester in northwest England sent him to trial
on Tuesday for Grundy's death and will decide on December 7
whether he should face trial for the others.
</P>
<P>
All four of the murders with which he is charged allegedly took
place between December last year and June this year.
</P>
<P>
Shipman is being held in prison until his trial begins with a
hearing on December 8, where he is due to make his plea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
