<DOCNO> XIE19981111.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Open Supermarkets in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, November 10 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's supermarket
group, Shoprite Checkers, has planned to open a large supermarket
network and fresh food stores in Angola.
</P>
<P>
The plan of Shoprite has won the approval of the Angolan
government the other day, the Angolan News Agency Angog reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The South African company has decided to invest 30.9 million
U.S. Dollars to set up three limited corporations in Angola from
1998 to 2000.
</P>
<P>
According to Shoprite's investment plan, 14.69 million Dollars
will go to Shoprite Supermarket, 12.77 million Dollars to
Shoprite Angola Real Estate and 3.44 million Dollars to Angola
Fresh Food Market.
</P>
<P>
Shoprite Supermarket is aimed at establishing a supermarket
network in Angola. Currently, it has plan to open eight
supermarkets and one big storage in capital Luanda, in Lobito in
central Angola and in Cabinda City in the north.
</P>
<P>
Shoprite Angola Real Estate is committed to the civil
construction and the post-war reconstruction. And it will deal
with the sales of real estates.
</P>
<P>
Angola Fresh Food Market will mainly process the produce and
supply goods to the various customers including the markets under
the Shoprite group.
</P>
<P>
The representative of Shoprite Checkers to Luanda noted that
the South African commercial group is interested in the market
potential in Angola, saying that its investment is only initial.
</P>
<P>
The group will enlarge its presense in Angola if the
performance of its outfits proves well, the representative added.
</P>
</TEXT>
