<HEADLINE> UN Holds Technical Meeting on Demographic Impact of  HIV/AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, November 10 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations on
Tuesday convened a Technical Meeting on the Demographic Impact on
HIV/AIDS.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the United Nations Population Division, in
collaboration with the Joint United Nations Program on HIV/AIDS,
the one-day meeting is to discuss current and future research
activities on the demographic impact of HIV/AIDS.
</P>
<P>
In a statement to the opening of the meeting, the United
Nations Deputy Secretary-General Louise Frechette said "HIV/AIDS
is a global human tragedy, which denies to the millions of its
victims the benefits of humanity's greatest achievement -- a
healthy, long life -- This indeed is one of the most serious
threats and challenges for the next century."
</P>
<P>
"The HIV/AIDS continues unabated, especially in developing
countries, particularly in sub-Saharan Africa, where AIDS now is
threatening the economic and social development gains that have
been painfully achieved during the past years," she said.
</P>
</TEXT>
