<HEADLINE> 4,398 Investment Projects licensed in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 10 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Investment
Authority announced Tuesday that 4,398 investment projects with a
total capital of 36.6 billion Birr (5.2 billion US Dollars) have
been licensed since the issuance of first investment code in May,
1992.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the inauguration of the World Investment Report
1998 at the United Nations Conference Center here, Tadesse Haile,
General Manager of the investment authority, said 1,184 of the
4,398 projects licensed in the stated period have entered into
their implementation phase.
</P>
<P>
Tadesse said these projects launched at a cost of 8.7 billion
Birr (1.2 billion US Dollars) have created 64,203 permanent jobs.
</P>
<P>
He said 706 other projects with a total capital of 6.2 billion
Birr (880 million US Dollars) are in the pipeline, while 152
projects with an aggregate capital of close to 8.3 billion Birr
(1.1 billion Dollars) are foreign investments in the areas of
agriculture, construction, education, health, hotel and tourism
and mining.
</P>
<P>
Tadesse also said Ethiopia has signed bilateral investment
promotion and protection agreements with several countries
including Italy, Kuwait, the Netherlands, Switzerland, China and
Germany, adding that the country is ready to sign similar
agreements with other countries.  
