<HEADLINE> Cyprus, France Sign Agreement on Road Transport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus and France signed here
Tuesday an agreement on international road transport, which is
expected to boost trade between the two countries as well as
between Cyprus and third countries.
</P>
<P>
The agreement provides for the exchange of licenses for cargo
transportation between the two countries or between Cyprus, or
France, and third countries.
</P>
<P>
Cypriot vehicles will be granted licenses to traverse France,
according to the agreement.
</P>
<P>
