<HEADLINE> Russia to Ban Import of Ethyl Alcohol </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Russia will ban the import of
ethyl alcohol until January 1, 2002, under a bill drafted by the
country's Trade Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The move, coupling with earlier measures of tighter controls
over the production of ethyl alcohol inside the country, will
place the Russian alcohol market under full state control, the
ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The ban on alcohol import will make it easier for law
enforcement agencies to supervise the sales of alcohol in border
areas as all imported alcohol will be regarded as contraband.
</P>
<P>
According to Russia's State Taxation Service, two thirds of the
alcoholic products reaching the market are illicit as a result of
smuggling, bootleg distillery and unauthorized sales of ethyl
alcohol, vodka and other strong drinks, causing major losses to
the Russian economy, Interfax reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
