<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2100GMT, November 10 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- British Secretary of State for Defense George
Robertson left Manama Tuesday for home following his brief one-day
visit to Bahrain, according to reports reaching Abu Dhabi.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Bahrain, Robertson held talks with senior
Bahraini officials on ways to develop and promote bilateral
relations, and the latest developments in the region, particularly
the current standoff between Iraq and the United Nations.
(BC-UK-Bahrain-Iraq)
</P>
