worker is asked to stay at home," he said, adding the government
is fueling the situation by deploying army and police officers in
response to the pending mass work boycott set for Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He advised all workers to stay at their homes to avoid
violence which the government may use to "militarize" the
situation.  
