<HEADLINE> World's Biggest Carpet Being Woven in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November 11 (Xinhua) -- A 5,000-square-meter carpet,
expected to be the largest in the world, is being woven in
Iran's northeastern province of Khorasan, the official Islamic
Republic News Agency reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ali-Asghar Zarandi, an official on carpet industry in the
province, said that the carpet is being woven in Baghshan village
by 200 female weavers, who complete 125 square meters each month.
</P>
<P>
Zarandi said that one third of the turquoise-colored carpet
has been woven with natural dyes in a period of nine months.
</P>
<P>
He said that the traditionally-designed carpet can fetch the
country 5 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Iran said the world's biggest carpet of 1,000
square meters was produced in Ben city in Iran's western province
of Chaharmahal-Bakhtiari. It was completed in three years by 84
weavers.
</P>
<P>
The carpet cost about 500 million rials (about 166,000
U.S. dollars) and was estimated to be priced above 1.2 billion
rials (about 400,000 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Iran is well-known for its traditional hand-woven carpet,
which ranks first in the country's non-oil exports. But during
recent years, the Iranian carpet industry was challenged by
products of China and India in the world market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
