Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien's upcoming visit to Russia,
set for next January, "is expected to positively influence the
development of Russian-Canadian relations."
</P>
<P>
The decision to postpone a Canadian trade and economic
mission, which was to accompany Chretien, in no way diminishes the
significance of the Canadian Prime Minister's visit to Russia.
</P>
<P>
"We attach great importance to this visit and are looking
forward to it," Ivanov said.
</P>
<P>
Axworthy, for his part, noted that the decision to postpone the
visit of the Canadian mission had been made by mutual agreement
between Moscow and Ottawa.
