<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Meets Asahi Shimbun President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 11 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin said
today that China and Japan will cooperate in shaping the framework
for the future of friendly Sino-Japanese relations.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president made the remark during a meeting with
Muneyuki Matsushita, president of Asahi Shimbun, a widely
circulated national newspaper in Japan.
</P>
<P>
Jiang added that the framework will be based on a review of
past and and an eye to the future.
</P>
<P>
This year marks the 20th anniversary of the signing of the
China-Japan Peace and Friendship Treaty and the Chinese president
is scheduled to pay a state visit to Japan beginning on November
25.
</P>
<P>
"The forthcoming visit will be extremely important," said
Jiang, adding that he expects to meet Japanese Emperor Akihito and
hold talks with Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi.
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed that Sino-Japanese relations will continue to
grow in a stable and sound manner so long as the two nations
strictly adhere to the spirit and principles of the treaty and
China-Japan joint statement to solve difference of opinion.
</P>
<P>
"Past experiences should be remembered and serve as a guide for
the future," said Jiang. He also expressed hope that the Japanese
side will adopt a correct attitude towards history and join hands
with China in creating a better future.
</P>
<P>
He praising the Japanese newspaper for the positive role it has
played in promoting bilateral friendship, and called on the
Japanese media to continue efforts to further promote relations
between the two nations.
</P>
<P>
Matsushita said Japanese citizens hold high hope for the
complete success of Jiang's forthcoming visit.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also briefed Matshuhita on China's reform and economic
growth, and addressed questions related to various international
and regional issues.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
