<HEADLINE> Vietnam, S. Korea Discuss Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, November 11 (Xinhua) -- South Korean Deputy Minister of
Foreign Affairs and Trade Choi Sung-Hong presented a number of
petitions by the country's businesses at the fifth meeting of the
Joint Economic Cooperation Committee which opened here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The south Korean official urged Vietnam to abandon
discrimination in service prices, remove tariff and non-tariff
barriers and ease regulations on import-export by joint ventures,
according to press reports.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese Deputy Minister of Planning and Investment Vo Hong
Phuc said Vietnam was considering easing visa formalities so as to
provide longer terms for foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
As regards forex management, the official said this was just a
situational solution at a time demand was running high but supply
was limited due to the regional turmoil.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics showed that by 1997, the two-way trade
between Vietnam and South Korea had quadrupled from 490 million
U.S. dollars in 1992.
</P>
<P>
However, their two-way trade has dropped 14 percent and
Vietnam's trade deficit has reached 938 million dollars out of a
total turnover of 1. 2 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Official figures also showed that South Korea has become the
fourth largest investor in Vietnam with 212 projects capitalized
at 3.21 billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
