<HEADLINE> France Won't Join Possible Air Strikes against Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 11 (Xinhua) -- France will not join possible
U.S. military strikes against Iraq under current circumstances,
said official sources here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse quoted the sources as saying that French
participation in military action against Iraq "under the
present state of things" is excluded.
</P>
<P>
The French government wants the United Nations Secretary
General Kofi Annan to fly to Baghdad immediately to defuse the
crisis, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
Such a move by the U.N. chief is preferred by Paris, although
his space to act is very small, they said.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, the United Nations withdrew the Baghdad staff of
the United Nations Special Commission (UNSCOM) in charge of
disarmament and the International Atomic Energy Agency in case of
a military conflict between the United States and Iraq. 
</P>
