Caroline Cross, left their Baghdad headquarters en route for the
Habbaniya airport, west of the capital, witnesses said. A UN
official, who did not want to be identified, told Xinhua that some
100 UNSCOM staff currently staying in Baghdad were asked in the
early Wednesday morning to go to the airport. They are expected to
fly back to New York through Bahrain.
