<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Bring District headquarters under Digital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will bring all the
district headquarters under digital telephone network by the year
2000, Telecommunications Minister Nohammad Nasim was quoted by the
official BSS news agency as saying in the parliament Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
So far, 15 out of the total 64 district headquarters have
already been brought under digital telephone technology, according
to the minister.
</P>
<P>
Besides, work to bring 80 sub-district headquarters under
digital telephone system has been undertaken, Nasim told the
house.
</P>
<P>
The government has broken monopoly in mobile telephone
operation giving licenses to several companies, he said, adding
his ministry "is still negotiating with the mobile operators to
extend maximum benefits to the subscribers including free incoming
calls."
</P>
<P>
The telephone service has developed rapidly in the country in
recent years. The total number of telephones in January 1998 was
492,000, while the total number in June 1996 is 117,000.
</P>
<P>
The government will provide the sector with 3.38 billion taka
(about 69.7 million U.S. dollars) in the public sector to
encourage the expansion of telecommunications in the current July
1998-June 1999 fiscal year, according to finance minister's annual
budget report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
