<HEADLINE> Shanghai Opens 1st Electronic On-Line Shop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Two local companies in
Shanghai on Tuesday opened the city's first on-line shop that
accepts credit card payment from Internet shoppers.
</P>
<P>
The buyers pay their bills by entering information such as
credit-card number, purchaser's name, and merchandise code number.
</P>
<P>
The transaction is completed automatically via a coded payment
module connected with outlets of the Shanghai Branch of the
Agricultural Bank of China, the issuer of two credit cards that
are accepted by the electronic shop.
</P>
<P>
The shop, which specializes in compact discs, is jointly
operated by the Shanghai EDI Industry Co., Ltd. and the China Book
Import and Export Company.
</P>
<P>
The shop is expected to accept cards issued by other local
banks as well as international cards such as VISA and MASTER CARD.
