<HEADLINE> Three Countries Undecided over Asian Games Participation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Three countries are yet to
confirm their participation in the 13th Asian Games next month,
said organizers on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Games advisory committee chairman Admiral Surawut Maharom said
Yemen, Tajikistan and Palestine had not confirmed their
attendance, warning that any delays could threaten the smooth
running of the event.
</P>
<P>
The main concern with the delay was for scheduling training
times for athletes and programming for live telecasts, said the
official.
</P>
<P>
Another concern was that draws also have to be planned well in
advance, he added.
</P>
<P>
Officials have shrugged off fears that Asia's financial crisis
would overshadow the event. But already, some of the 41 competing
nations have been forced to scale down their teams, blaming
economic woes. 
