<DOCNO> XIE19981111.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Industrial Growth Declines in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 11 (Xinhua) -- India's industrial growth
rates went down to 1.4 percent in September, thus bringing the
overall industrial growth in the first six months of the current
fiscal year beginning from April 1 to 3.6 percent from 6 percent
during the same period last year, according to figures released by
the Indian government here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The overall growth rate of 1.4 percent in September 1998 was
far below the 8.5 percent recorded in the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
All three major sub-sectors in the Index of Industrial
Production (IIP) -- manufacturing, mining and electricity --
showed sharp decline in September as compared to that of the
previous month.
</P>
<P>
Manufacturing grew by only 2 percent compared to 4.2 percent in
August and 8.7 percent reached in the fiscal year 1997-98.
</P>
<P>
Electricity grew by 2.6 percent as against 6.8 percent recorded
in the previous month and 9.3 percent in September 1997 while
mining recorded a negative 4.9 percent compared to 0.6 percent in
August and 5.2 percent a year earlier, the figures showed.
</P>
<P>
Poor performance in September had further pulled down
cumulative growth figures with the manufacturing sector growth
declining to 3.4 percent from 6 percent a year ago and mining
sector posting negative growth of 0.4 percent in the first half
compared to 5 percent last year.
</P>
<P>
However, growth of electricity showed a small improvement over
last year at 7.7 percent compared to 7.2 percent during the
April-September period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Both consumer durables and non-durables posted negative growth
rates of 2.5 and 5.2 percent in September compared to 9.8 and 12.2
percent reached respectively last September.
</P>
<P>
Basic goods also had a negative growth of 1.4 percent in
September resulting in half-yearly growth of 2.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
There was some improvement in growth rates of capital goods and
intermediate goods in September at 8.5 and 8.2 percent
respectively compared to 7.2 and 7.1 percent in August. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
