<HEADLINE> IOC Drug List Need Radical Overhaul: Expert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Doping expert Dr. Ken Fitch
said Wednesday that the drug list of the International Olympic
Committee (IOC) need a "radical" overhaul, including the removal
of some narcotics from the banned list.
</P>
<P>
Fitch, who is on the medical commissions for both the IOC and
Sydney Olympic organizers SOCOG, said in Sydney he agreed with
the comments by IOC president Juan Antonio Samaranch earlier this
year that the banned list needed simplification.
</P>
<P>
"President Samaranch's comments have thrown open our chances
to have a more radical look at the list than we have in recent
years," Fitch said.
</P>
<P>
Mainly drugs like morphine, pethidine needed to be slashed
from the banned list, Fitch said, adding that heroin would remain
on the list. 
</P>
</TEXT>
