<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, November 11 (Xinhua) -- The Lao people's Democratic
Republic and the Republic of Georgia agreed to establish
diplomatic relations at the ambassadorial level on November 6, Lao
official news agency KPL reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the protocol, which was signed in Moscow, the Lao
People's Democratic Republic and the Republic of Georgia
established their diplomatic relations in the spirit of expanding
the friendly relations and the cooperation in the domains of
politics, economy, commerce, culture, humanitarian affairs, and
others.
</P>
<P>
The protocol was signed by Thouane Vorasane, Lao ambassador to
the Federation of Russia, and Malichas Kakabre, Georgian
ambassador to Russia.
</P>
<P>
KPL said that the protocol on the establishment of the
diplomatic ties reflects the satisfaction of the two countries
over the expansion of the bilateral relations on the basis of the
respect of mutual sovereignty, equality, territorial integrity,
and non-interference in the domestic affairs of each other.
</P>
