<HEADLINE> Greater Environmental Protection Efforts Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Zou Jiahua, Vice-Chairman of
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, has
called for a correct handling of the relationship between economic
development and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Zou made this call during an inspection tour of environmental
protection projects in Hangzhou, the capital of Zhejiang Province,
from November 9 to 11. He also urged the use of more high-
technology for environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
"Environmental protection is a basic Chinese national policy,
and the relationship between resources and the environment should
be perceived from a strategic height," Zou said, after visiting
the Hangzhou Sibao Sewage Treatment Plant and several other
environmental protection projects in Hangzhou, an important
industrial and tourist city on China's east coast.
</P>
<P>
"We should rationally develop and comprehensively utilize
resources and protect and improve the environment to make good the
strategy of rejuvenating the country through science and education,
and the strategy of sustained growth," Zou said.
</P>
<P>
On hearing that Hangzhou leads other Chinese cities in the use
of methane generated by rubbish dumps for power generation, Zou
said that much can be done in environmental protection when high-
technology is employed.
</P>
<P>
Zou also said that both legislative and law enforcement efforts
should be increased to curb pollution in the Beijing-Hangzhou
Grand Canal.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Zhejiang, Zou also visited the Qinshan
Nuclear Power Station. He said efforts must be made for
environmental protection in the process of the peaceful use of
nuclear energy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
