<HEADLINE> Sdyney Wants Athletes Tested Before Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Australia wants pre-Olympic
testing over competitors as soon as they settle in the Olympic
village ahead of the Sdyney 2000 Games.
</P>
<P>
"The IOC have been saying we don't take precedence over these
athletes until the Games start but in actual fact we do," said
IOC medical commission member Dr Ken Fitch in a conference in
Sdyney.
</P>
<P>
"Once the village opens they have to comply with village rules
and it makes no sense to me that we can't test."
</P>
<P>
The IOC stopped pre-Olympic testing after the 1976 Montreal
Games and failed in their attempts to reintroduce the tests for
the 1996 Atlanta Games.
</P>
<P>
Fitch said he planned to push his case at the next IOC
Commission meeting. 
