<HEADLINE> Cuba, China Sail into Final at Volleyball Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OSAKA, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Cuba beat Brazil 3-1 while
China crushed Russia 3-0 in the women's semifinals here on
Wednesday to set up a rematch of the Atlanta Olympic Games final
at the World Volleyball Championships.
</P>
<P>
Cuba's 15-10, 4-15, 15-11 and 15-10 victory over the South
Americans repeated their triumphs in the 1994 world championship
final and in the semifinal at Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
China, world champions in 1982 and 1986, needed only 80
minutes to sweep past the Russians 15-4, 15-4, 15-9 and won the
chance to avenge their loss to the Cubans in the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Before the match, the Russian team had a perfect winning
record through the group competitions and second-phase
competitions.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, which booked their semi-final berth thanks
to Bulgaria's surprise victory over South Korea, played their
best match in recent years.
</P>
<P>
They dominated the match throughout with their tight blocking,
powerful smashing and effective team combination.
</P>
<P>
The Russian team, to the contrary, suddenly found they lost
their winning touch in the group competitions and committed lots
of mistakes.
</P>
<P>
After losing the first two sets with an identical score of
15-4, the Russian team again lagged 12-3 behind. They fought
desperately and narrowed the gap to 12-9 but their Chinese rivals
again pulled away to wrap up the match 15-9.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team will play Cuba in the final on Thursday.
</P>
</TEXT>
