<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fewer New Firms Set Up in Macao in First 9 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, November 11 (Xinhua) -- A total of 379 companies were
established here in the first nine months of the year, a decline
of 31 percent from the same period of 1997, latest official
statistics show.
</P>
<P>
The capital of the new companies added up to 109.3 million
patacas (13.66 million U.S. dollars), a decrease of 8.9 percent
compared with that of the same period last year, according to
figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In the third quarter of the year, 128 companies were set up, a
drop of 25.1 percent from the same season of 1997 but an increase
of 4.9 percent over the second season of this year.
</P>
<P>
The new companies are engaged mainly in wholesale and retail,
catering services, maintenance of vehicles, motorcycles and
personal and domestic goods. Other businesses cover fields of
construction, education, medical care and social services.
</P>
<P>
Between July and September of the year, 13 companies were
dissolved.
</P>
<P>
The decline in the number of new firms was believed to be the
result of a continuous slowdown of the economic growth in Macao as
well as in its surrounding areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
