<HEADLINE> Passenger Arrivals to Macao Rise in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Passenger arrivals to Macao by
means of marine, land and air routes reached 517,391 in September
this year, up four percent over the same month of 1997, according
to figures issued Wednesday by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department.
</P>
<P>
The figures indicate that total passenger arrivals in the first
nine months of the year decreased two percent compared with the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Between January and September, passengers from the Chinese
mainland and China's Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
accounted for 76.1 percent of the entire number entering Macao,
an increase of 7.5 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
In comparison, passengers from the Republic of Korea, Japan,
Southeast Asia and South Asia plunged to a great extent. The
decline is believed to be a result of the lasting financial crisis
 in these areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
