<HEADLINE> Macao Police Make Holiday Plan for Smooth Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, November 11 (Xinhua) -- The Public Security Police
Division of Macao has promulgated a decree requiring that all
police use up their vacation before October 31 next year so as to
ensure smooth handover affairs.
</P>
<P>
According to the decree, police cannot have leaves in November
or December of next year, as the handover ceremony will be held on
December 20 marking Macao's power transfer from Portugal to China.
</P>
<P>
Police officers are asked to map out an overall plan to give
leave permission to their subordinates so that the normal work of
their sections will not be affected.
</P>
<P>
The Public Security Police Division is the first government
body in Macao to issue a decree requesting appropriate leaves
next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
