<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Surge 4.28 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed
sharply higher Wednesday boosted by active overseas buying.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index surged 415.99 points, or 4.28 percent,
to close at 10,137.32 Wednesday. Turnover jumped to 7.821 billion
HK dollars (one billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Securities analysts said that foreign funds from the United
States and Europe flooded into the market, which eased nearly 800
points over the past four trading days. A sharp rise in Hang Seng
Index Futures also helped lift the market.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip index shrugged off an opening loss, and
maintained the gaining momentum to close at the highest of the
day, 10,137.32 points.
</P>
<P>
Property shares surged 926.20 points, or 7.25 percent, to
lead Wednesday's cross-the-board rise. Commercial and industrial
stocks rose 5.66 percent, or 325 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
