<HEADLINE> Uganda Central Bank Sacks Directors of UCB </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, November 11 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of Uganda has sacked
three senior officials of Uganda Commercial Bank (UCB) for
facilitating transactions of Greenland Bank in it.
</P>
<P>
A letter was delivered to UCB Tuesday during its board
meeting, the New Vision paper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a resident supervisor from the central bank was
also put into the UCB to ensure that the bank is properly run.
</P>
<P>
Joseph Chong, the chairman of Westmont company which manages
UCB, said general managers of branch banking, credit division and
international division were removed from office.
</P>
<P>
He denied reports of a link-up between UCB and Greenland Bank
and welcomed the central bank's move to monitor his bank,
asserting that he had never seen any sale agreement between
Greenland and Westmont.
</P>
<P>
However, he admitted grilling the UCB chief executive Vijayan
Anandan over the loans to the Greenland Group of Companies.
</P>
<P>
There has been widespread allegation that Greenland Investment
Limited connived with Westmont to buy UCB. Some government
officials have confirmed that Westmont transferred all the 49
percent shares to UCB it has bought to Greenland immediately.
Westmont only manages the bank and does not own a single share.
</P>
</TEXT>
