<HEADLINE> CPC Leader Meets South African Communist Party Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Chunyun, a member of the
Political Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee,
met today with a delegation from the South African Communist Party
headed by Secretary General Blade Nzimande.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
Chinese National People's Congress, said the two parties have
enjoyed long-term relations and and friendship cultivated through
years of arduous struggle.
</P>
<P>
He said the delegation's visit would further tighten relations
between the two countries and parties.
</P>
<P>
Jiang briefed the delegation on China's political system, the
development of the socialist democracy and legal system, and the
nation's current political and economic situation. 
</P>
