<HEADLINE> Environmental Education Center Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 11 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Environmental
Education Center was established here today by the World Fund for
Nature, the China Association of Science and Technology and the
Beijing Municipal Association of Science and Technology.
</P>
<P>
The center features activity and lecture halls, a reading room
and a video center, an exhibition hall and an open-air training
facility.
</P>
<P>
The center plans to host a series of scientific promotions
activities, including lectures, experiments, investigations,
competitions and academic seminars related to environmental
resources and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Plans also call for the center will hold regular summer and
winter camps for environmental investigation, animal husbandry,
farming and ecology. Related activities will be held in the city's
21 environmental bases.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the center has introduced the nation's first
international training program for environmental instructors.
</P>
</TEXT>
