<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IPR System Faces Impact of Digital Technology (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The basic principle for handling intellectual property issues
resulting from digital technology centers on maintaining balanced
interests, said Ying.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the fundamental purpose for establishing IPR
system was to protect the legal interests of creators and
distributors and encourage both creativity and distribution of
works, as well as to ensure public access, fulfill the needs of
the general public, enhance civilization and promote progress.
</P>
<P>
Numerous countries are now devoting major efforts to
constructing the information highway. Any failure to protect
intellectual property rights for products, including cultural and
entertainment products, distributed on the information highway
will prevent fill realization of the ultimate potential capacity
of the medium, said Ying.
</P>
<P>
Yang Xiaoguang, deputy director general of the Patent and
Trademark Law Office under the China Council for Promotion of
International Trade, said that "the development of computer
network technology demands a higher level protection for computer
programs."
</P>
<P>
He noted that "the Law on Copyrights has played an important
role in protecting computer program, but the most effective means
continues to be patent protection.
</P>
<P>
"China should further study patent protection for computer
programs related to invention, provide specific definition and
explanations to related questions, and ensure software developers
understand types of patentable computer programs."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
