<DOCNO> XIE19981111.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzanian President Reaffirms Decision of Moving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, November 11 (Xinhua) - Tanzanian President
Benjamin Mkapa has reaffirmed that his government is determined
to move the capital to the central city of Dodoma though it is
backward in social services.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa told a rally while on a tour of the Dodoma Region
Tuesday that as Tanzania's economy is reviving slowly, the Dodoma
City will be built into the new capital gradually.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted Wednesday by the press as saying that starting
with the newly established Ministry of Local Governments and
Regional Administration, more ministries will move to Dodoma, 450
km west of Dar es Salaam.
</P>
<P>
The president said that from now on, he will spend more time
at the Chamwino presidential lodge in Dodoma, especially when he
is free from state activities in Dar es Salaam.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa said that he will also invite donor nations and agencies
to fund the construction of Dodoma as a national development
project.
</P>
<P>
Sitting at the heart of Tanzania at an altitude of 1,133
meters above sea level, Dodoma has been designated as the new
capital since Tanzania got independence in early 1960s.
</P>
<P>
Dodoma, formerly a small settlement of the Wa-Gogo Tribe, is
also a major stop of the Central Railway Line.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
