<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed higher Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index was up
8.58 points to 476.12, the all-share Emas Index rose 2.33 points
to 125.50, the Industrial Index added 16.81 points to 900.23 while
the Second Board Index fell 0.64 of a point to 139.36.
</P>
<P>
Gainers outnumbered losers by 500 to 240 while 103 counters
were unchanged, 77 untraded and 42 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased 568.806 million shares valued at
859.412 million ringgit (226.161 million U.S. dollars) from
350.225 million shares valued at 553.867 million ringgit (about
145.754 million dollars) Tuesday. 
</P>
