<HEADLINE> China Releases Trade Figures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 11 (Xinhua) -- China's total trade hit 259.1
billion US dollars in the first ten months of this year, up 0.4
percent on last year's same period, according to the General
Administration of Customs.
</P>
<P>
Exports during that period grew by 1.3 percent to 148.8 US
billion dollars, whereas imports dropped by 0.7 percent to end the
period at 110.3 billion.
</P>
<P>
The trade surplus hit 38.4 billion US dollars, up 7.8 percent
on the same 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
exports fell by 17.3 percent in October to 14.73 billion US
dollars, and imports by 9.2 percent to 11.65 billion US
dollars. 
</P>
