<HEADLINE> Foreigners Residing in S. Korea Number 291,816 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Foreigners residing in South
Korea numbered 291,816 as of the end of August of this year,
including 92,686 illegalities, according to the Justice Ministry
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In terms of nationality, China topped the list, with 108,819,
followed by the United States with 51,579 (excluding the 38,000
U.S. troops in South Korea), Japan 27,235, and other nations
104,183.
</P>
<P>
Most of the Chinese in the country are Chinese Koreans who came
seeking employment as technical trainees under a government alien
employment program.
</P>
<P>
Foreigners staying for more than 90 days with an alien
registration card numbered 148,926 and those staying for less than
90 days on a short term visa came to 142,890.
</P>
<P>
Of the long-term stayers, 67,361 were in the government's alien
training program, 30,125 were overseas Koreans with foreign
citizenships and 22,600 were those who married Koreans.
</P>
<P>
In the first eight months of this year, 7,590 aliens were
refused entry for holding forged passports or violations of the
South Korean immigration law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
