<HEADLINE> UNSCOM Staff Ordered to Pull out of Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, November 11 (Xinhua) -- The UN Special Commission in
charge of Iraq's disarmament (UNSCOM) was ordered Wednesday to
pull out of Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Three buses full of UNSCOM staff, including spokeswoman
Caroline Cross, left their Baghdad headquarters en route for
the Habbaniya airport, west of the capital, witnesses said.
</P>
<P>
A UN official, who did not want to be identified, told Xinhua
that some 100 UNSCOM staff currently staying in Baghdad were asked
in the early morning of Wednesday to go to the airport. They are
expected to fly back to New York through Bahrain, he added.
</P>
<P>
From November 7, the UNSCOM has arranged its staff to withdraw
from Iraq in two groups, a sign that the United States and Britain
will probably launch a military strike on Iraq, some analysts
said. 
