<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Measures Add Convenience to Hong Kong Business Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 11 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Public
Security's Exit-Entry Administration has issued a series of
policies and measures adding convenience to the Hong Kong business
activities of inland enterprises and individuals.
</P>
<P>
The policies and measures include simplified application
procedures. Qualified enterprise staffers with approved
applications will only need to provide personal information on an
annual basis.
</P>
<P>
The time required for examinations and approvals has been
shortened to enable applicants to visit Hong Kong during specified
periods.
</P>
<P>
Provinces with a large amount of applicants will transfer the
examination and approval authority from the provincial
government to either their capitals or major cities.
</P>
<P>
Revised application requirements enable more inland enterprises
and individuals to conduct business activities in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Limits involving valid periods and times for transit visas have
been abolished. All exit-entry administrations have the authority
to approve applications within the total quotas, in accordance
with the documented needs of applicants.
</P>
<P>
Priority will be given to enterprise staffers who have
consistently adhered to entry and exit laws.
</P>
<P>
Administration officials noted that Chinese staffers with
China-based branches of international organizations, foreign
embassies and enterprises, media organizations and inland
residents working for joint ventures, collectively-owned
businesses and private enterprises can apply to local exit-entry
administration for visiting Hong Kong for training or
business.
</P>
<P>
The administration requires all pertinent organizations to
publicize related procedures, policies, and regulations in order
to ensure convenient supervision of examination and approval
procedures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
