headquarters in Damascus as Syria has pledged to ban PKK's
activities in its territories.
</P>
<P>
Sabah (Morning):
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish State Minister for economic affairs Gunes Taner
said Tuesday that 1999 will be "a difficult year" for Turkey in
terms of economy because of the economic depression in Russia and
many Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Turkey would take a series of positive measures
to overcome the disadvantages in order to achieve its economic
goals. 
