<HEADLINE> S. African Airways to Begin Flying to Lagos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, November 11 (Xinhua) -- South African Airways
(SAA), Africa's biggest air carrier, will begin flying from
Johannesburg to Nigeria's commercial capital Lagos later this
month, Business Day paper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The company planned the Lagos move early this year as part of
the company's strategy to return to profitability, a SAA
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The airline reported a loss of 207 million Rand (37 million
U.S. Dollars) in the six months to September, 43 percent more
than that in the same period last year. The company last
registered a profit in 1995.
</P>
<P>
"West Africa is one of the fastest growing commercial hubs for
us, and Lagos is the biggest commercial center in West Africa,"
the spokesman said.  
</P>
