<HEADLINE> International Elevator Exposition In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 11 (Xinhua) -- The Third International
Elevator Show opened today at the Beijing Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
Companies from the United States, Canada, Switzerland, Japan,
Taiwan, and about a dozen other countries and regions are
displaying their products at the four-day event.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland's Schindler is showing its newest escalators, the
Schindler 9300 and Schindler 300P, which is designed for the Asia
market.
</P>
<P>
Schindler was one of the first companies to enter the China
market and has a fifth of China's elevator business, and annual
sales in China of more than 4,200 elevators.
</P>
<P>
Simon Ho, president of China-Schindler Co. Ltd., says that
China's elevator market has not only focused on quality and
advanced technology, but on service, so China-Schindler will
emphasize service during the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
China-Schindler was founded in 1980 and is the second oldest
Sino-foreign joint venture in China.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will help Chinese manufacturers see foreign
technology and provide foreigners more business opportunities in
China, says Du Zonghan, president of the China Elevator
Association. 
</P>
