<HEADLINE> Myanmar Athletes Win 190 Medals in Last Two Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar athletes won a total
of 190 medals during the last two years after the Ministry of
Sports was established in December 1996 and 63 sports contingents
sent abroad for contests since then.
</P>
<P>
The medals included 61 gold, 64 silver and 65 bronze. Of
them, two golds, two silvers and five bronzes were won by Myanmar
women weightlifters in the 11th International Women Weighlifting
Competition held in Chiangmai, Thailand, and a gold medal taken
by Ma Soe Soe Mya (female) in the world's Taekwondo Tournament in
Seoul, South Korea, in August this year.
</P>
<P>
At a graduation ceremony of the sports diploma course of the
Institute of Sports and Physical Education here Tuesday,
Lieutenant-General Khin Nyunt, first secretary of the Myanmar
State Peace and Development Council, urged newly trained Myanmar
athletes to make concerted efforts to enable Myanmar sports to
secure a place in the world as it did in the past and work hard
in unison to realize the objective "Myanmar Sports -- the World
to Conquer".
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt, who is also chairman of the Myanmar National
Olympic Council, said that Myanmar has set the objective in its
sports promotion program which is being carried out with strong
conviction, firm determination and added momentum.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar formed the Ministry of Sports to facilitate the sports
promotion program and set up the National Olympic Council and the
Olympic Committee to provide close supervision for the
activities. 
</P>
