<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Starts Construction of Largest Ore Transit Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, November 11 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Baoshan Steel
Group started this week the construction of the Majishan Ore
Transit Port, the largest deep-water transit port in the country.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the 250,000-ton--handling-capacity project
will cost 1.7 billion yuan and it includes a 250,000-ton unloading
berth, a 35,000-ton loading dock, a 1.2-million ton storage area
and other support facilities.
</P>
<P>
The port will be built on Sijiao Island in Zhejiang Province,
near Shanghai, where the steel complex is located.
</P>
<P>
The port project is part of a third-phase project of the steel
group, which is costing 60 billion yuan. The project is designed
to handle 20 million tons of ores annually.  
</P>
</TEXT>
