<HEADLINE> Large Nature Park to Be Built in Southwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Sichuan Province has decided
to build a large nature park in the Wolong Giant Panda Nature
Reserve and Siguniang (Four Girls) Mountain.
</P>
<P>
Two to three billion yuan (about 360 million U.S. dollars) is
needed for the 1,560-square-kilometer park, which will be one of
the largest in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Siguniang Mountain is 300 kilometers from Chengdu, capital of
the southwestern province and has snowy features and unusual animal
species like the giant panda and golden monkey, while Wolong Nature
Reserve is home to over 100 giant pandas.
</P>
<P>
The new nature park will be a tourist attraction for the
province.
</P>
<P>
A highway connecting Chengdu with the park is under
construction.  
</P>
