<HEADLINE> China's October Foreign Exchange Trade At 3.52 Billion U.S. Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's foreign exchange
market did 3.52 billion U.S. dollars worth of trade in October.
</P>
<P>
This included 3.344 billion U.S. dollars, 1.061 billion Hong
Kong dollars, and 5.544 billion Japanese yen. Only these three
currencies are traded on the Shanghai Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese yuan against the U.S. dollar and the Hong Kong
dollar remained stable in October, with the U.S. dollar being
quoted at 8.2778 yuan at the end of last month, down two points
from the end of September. The Hong Kong dollar ended October at
1.0673 yuan, almost unchanged from the end of September.
</P>
<P>
The yen was affected by the U.S. dollar's slide against the
yen, and gained markedly against the yuan last month on the
interbank foreign exchange market. The yen was trading at 7.1426
yuan per 100 yen at the end of October, up from 6.1247 yuan at the
end of September. 
