<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian Government Urged to Continue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, November 11, (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government has
been urged to continue its economic privatization program as this
is the only way to put the country's economy on the right track.
</P>
<P>
Local newspaper Times of Zambia Wednesday quoted Chairman of
Lusaka Chamber of Commerce and Industry (LCCI), Gaudenzio Rossi,
as saying that Zambia will only develop through the privatization
of the state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks after his Vice Chairman for Industry Henry
Chipewo recently appealed on the government to discontinue with
the privatization, alleging that the exercise does not benefit
the country but only benefits foreigners.
</P>
<P>
Rossi said that discontinuing the program at this stage will
only spell economic doom because the government has no financial
resources to recapitalize companies.
</P>
<P>
"This is a harsh program and there are many casualties on the
way but once completed it will bear fruit and people should
accept the fact that privatization is the only way out for us,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
He said it is true that some privatized companies have closed
down but this is not an indication that the exercise has failed
because the only solution for some companies is liquidation.
</P>
<P>
Rossi said the official position of LCCI is in support of the
program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
