<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Promotes Public Bidding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, November 11 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province
reported initial success in introducing public bidding for local
construction projects at the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
The province accepted public bids for 76 percent of all
construction projects between January and October this year, with
the process reducing investment costs by some 800 million yuan, or
close to four percent of costs under previous practices.
</P>
<P>
The local government has also strengthened effort to supervise
market order and public bidding process. The number of projects
subject to public bidding jumped 71 percent on last year's same
period.
</P>
<P>
The communications and postal services sectors have paid
special attention to public bidding for their complicated
investment and management systems. Trade centers handling
construction projects have been established so supervise public
bids.  
</P>
</TEXT>
