<HEADLINE> Donations Help Poor Gansu Residents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Donations totalling eight
million yuan (close to one million US dollars) have helped build
13,226 cisterns and have basically provided potable water to over
58,000 poverty-stricken farmers in Gansu Province, northwest China.
</P>
<P>
The China Charity Foundation received donations from both
inside and outside China.
</P>
<P>
The province succeeded in supply potable drinking water to six
million rural residents by the end of 1995.
</P>
<P>
Projects in recent years have completed 520,000 cisterns and
provided potable water to an additional 1.31 million people and
1.18 million head of livestock.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that one cistern has the capacity to collect 15
tons of water needed to sustain a family of five for 300 days.
</P>
<P>
The success of the previous projects prompted the federation to
undertake the most donation drive.  
</P>
