<HEADLINE> Lanzhou-Baotou Railway Electrification Project Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, November 11 (Xinhua) -- The project to electrify the
final section of the railway line running from Baotou in north
China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region to Lanzhou, capital of
northwest China's Gansu Province, was recently completed.
</P>
<P>
Electrification has brought an end to the operation of steam
locomotives along the 989-km railway line which was built in 1958
and has since served as one of the most important railway trunk
lines in north China.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government allocated more than two billion yuan to
electrify the final 567-km section of the line.
</P>
<P>
Traffic capacity on the improved railway is expected to double
and trains are expected to reach the speed of 100 km per hour, up
substantially on the previous 60 km per hour.
</P>
<P>
The electrified railway line is expected to further promote
economic development in western parts of the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
