<HEADLINE> China Enter Final of Women's Volleyball Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUKUOKA, November 11 (Xinhua) -- China entered the final of
the women's volleyball World Championship after trouncing Russia
3-0 on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, which had conceded two losses earlier in the
tournament, displayed a sparkling performance, beating their
higher and stronger Russia opponents 15-4, 15-4, 15-9 in just
over one hour.
</P>
<P>
Before the match, the Russian team had a perfect record
through the group competitions and second-phase competitions.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, which booked their semi-final berth thanks
to Bulgaria's surprise victory over South Korea, played their
best match in recent years.
</P>
<P>
They dominated the match throughout with their tight blocking,
powerful smashing and effective team combination.
</P>
<P>
The Russian team, to the contrary, suddenly found they lost
their winning touch in the group competitions and committed lots
of mistakes.
</P>
<P>
After losing the first two sets with an identical score of
15-4, the Russian team again lagged 12-3 behind. They fought
desperately and narrowed the gap to 12-9 but their Chinese rivals
again pulled away to wrap up the match 15-9.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team will play the final against the winners of
another semi-final match between Cuba and Brazil. 
</P>
</TEXT>
