<HEADLINE> ADB Provides Grant to Boost Agriculture Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 11 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank said
here Wednesday that it will provide a 5.6 million U.S. dollar
grant to five centers of the Consultative Group on International
Agricultural Research (CGIAR).
</P>
<P>
The ADB said that the assistance will help the five centers
develop environmentally sustainable farming system, and improve
crop varieties and technologies to increase agricultural
productivity and farm incomes.
</P>
<P>
The five centers which will share the grant are: the Center of
International Forestry Research in Bogor, Indonesia; the
International Crops Research Institute for Semi-Arid Tropics in
Hyderabad, India; the International Irrigation Management
Institute in Colombo, Sri Lanka; the International Livestock
Research Institute in Nairobi, Kenya; and the International Rice
Research Institute in Los Banos, the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
CGIAR was established in 1971 to provide financial support to
16 international agricultural research centers in developing
countries in Asia, Africa and Latin America. 
</P>
</TEXT>
