<HEADLINE> Meningitis Spreads in Zimbabwean Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Harare, Zimbabwe's capital,
has recorded 62 cases of meningitis, the daily Herald reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Health and Child Welfare Timothy Stamps said in an
interview that the significant spread of the disease in
over-crowded prisons in Harare, with poor standards of living,
has prompted his ministry to vaccinate all prisoners at Harare
Central, Chikurubi and Bindura prisons.
</P>
<P>
Stamps said at least three of the 12 people who died from
meningitis recently were serving prisoners and another 74 are
suffering from the disease countrywide.
</P>
<P>
The minister told the paper that his ministry had so far
vaccinated 3,000 inmates at Harare Central, Kurubi and another
500 prisoners were vaccinated at Bindura prison.  
</P>
</TEXT>
