<HEADLINE> Jiangxi Set to Begin Second Phase Poyang Lake Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, November 11 (Xinhua) -- The second phase of a project
to control flooding on Poyang Lake in east China's Jiangxi
Province will commerce within the year.
</P>
<P>
The central government has allocated the initial 160 million
yuan for the five-year project.
</P>
<P>
Plans call for reinforcing 15 levees which are vital for
ensuring safety in the lake area and protect more than 3,333
hectares of cultivated land. Warning systems and auxiliary flood
control facilities will be introduced.
</P>
<P>
The first phase project, which commenced in 1986, focused on
improving levees and flood diversion areas.
</P>
<P>
Levees stretching some 662 km were reinforced and protected
over 6,666 hectares of cultivated fields during this year's
devastating flooding along the Yangtze River.  
</P>
</TEXT>
