<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Exports Earn Record 3.4 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's export sector
earned a record 3.4 billion U.S. dollars during the first nine
months of this year, a 15.2 percent rise over the same period of
1997.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ministry of Industrial Development Wednesday,
this performance was a result of the attractive incentives offered
to export oriented industries by the government.
</P>
<P>
Accordingly the industrialists were able to modernize and
upgrade their industries. Existing industries had also been able
to expand due to the incentives.
</P>
<P>
From January to September, agricultural exports contributed 810
million U.S. dollars, which is a growth of 18 percent. Industrial
exports grew by 16.1 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The textiles and apparel sector grew by 21.2 percent and the
leather and rubber goods sector grew by 21.3 percent over the same
period of 1997. 
</P>
