<HEADLINE> Non-Government Enterprises in Southwestern China Doing Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Non-government science and
technology enterprises in southwest China's Sichuan Province have
been growing and become a force for local economic development.
</P>
<P>
The number of enterprises here went from 1,831 in 1992 to 3,368
in 1997, with the number of employees growing from 41,000 to more
than 100,000.
</P>
<P>
Non-government science and technology enterprises had 11.8
billion yuan in gross income in 1997, of them 29 each had an
annual income of more than 100 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
A group of local non-government enterprises have expanded by
re-organizing assets, cooperating with state businesses, and
merging.
</P>
<P>
Last year, non-government science and technology enterprises
made 46 million U.S. dollars in foreign exchange from exports, a
nearly 77 percent rise from the 1996 level.  
</P>
