between the two countries. In August last year, Myanmar and
Singapore specialists successfully performed cardiac operations
for the first time in Yangon's Defense Services General Hospital
by inserting balloon catheters in the hearts of four
cardiovascular patients.
</P>
<P>
As a follow-up, the Myanmar surgeons are planning to treat
cardiac patients effectively by using cardiovascular X-ray system
provided by Japan.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Myanmar specialists also successfully transplanted
for the first time a kidney on a 41-year old woman in May last
year, according to earlier official report. 
