<HEADLINE> Bangkok Taxi Drivers Trained to Serve Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Taxi drivers in Thailand's
capital are to undergo special training courses to help them
deliver a better quality of service to tourists, a press release
from the Tourism Authority of Thailand (TAT) available Wednesday
said.
</P>
<P>
The first batch of 31 drivers sat for their training between
November 5-7, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
The "Tourist Taxi" training project includes training of
tourist taxi drivers in language skills, foreign cultures and
behavior with foreigners. It will also help expand taxi drivers'
knowledge of hotel locations and tourist cultural spots.
</P>
<P>
On completing their training, the drivers will get "Tourist
Taxi" windscreen stickers and certificates. In addition, "Tourist
Survival Cards" will be available in taxis, containing a listing
of essential phone numbers, language tips and a map showing
important tourist attractions in Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
A "Taxi-Driver of the Month" reward will be presented every
month to the driver who receives the most positive feedback from
passengers.
</P>
<P>
From January to August this year, international visitor
arrivals to Thailand surged by 5.59 percent to over five million
from 4.77 million in the same period last year. About 80 percent
of all visitors to Thailand come through Bangkok. 
</P>
