<HEADLINE> Brazil's Coffee Exports Up 56 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Brazil has exported 7.3
million bags (60 kilograms each) of coffee in the July-October
period, a 56-percent increase over the same period last year, the
Folha de Sao Paulo newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
But the exports earnings were only 894.9 million U.S. dollars,
down by 4.9 percent, as prices on the international market dipped
from last year's high on an excess of demand, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
In October, Brazil exported two million bags of coffee, earning
230 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's coffee output this year is expected to reach the best
harvest in 10 years -- between 34 and 36 million bags, including
11 million bags for export.
</P>
<P>
The country is the world's biggest coffee producer and
exporter. 
