<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment Increases in Northern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, November 11 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
province now has 5,120 overseas-funded enterprises involving a
total investment of 7.2 billion U.S. dollars, latest statistics
show.
</P>
<P>
More than 170 of these enterprises were opened this year. There
are 98 each with 10 million U.S. dollars investment or more,
accounting for more than half the investment of local
overseas-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The overseas funding is coming from 92 countries and regions,
with Hong Kong topping the list in volume, followed by Singapore,
the U.S., Britain, and Canada.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 2,000 overseas-backed enterprises are involved in
agriculture, wholesale and retail sales, food service, and
entertainment.
</P>
<P>
So far this year, productive joint ventures in the province
reported a total output value of 41 billion yuan, a 21 percent
rise from a year earlier, with their combined sales increasing 29
percent to 51 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
In the ten-month period, overseas-funded enterprises here added
more than 800 million yuan to their investment, up 30 percent from
the same 1997 period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
