<HEADLINE> Lettuce, Garlic Center in Northwestern Chinese Basin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, November 11 (Xinhua) -- The Qaidam Basin on the
Qinghai-Tibet Plateau is being turned into a major lettuce- and
garlic-growing center for Qinghai Province and the rest of the
country.
</P>
<P>
With its long periods of strong sunshine and differences in
temperatures from day to night, the Basin is especially good for
growing lettuce and garlic from July to September, when the
weather in southern parts of China is less suitable.
</P>
<P>
This year, one farm in the city of Golmud planted 600 mu (40
hectares) of lettuce and had a per-mu output of 2,500
kilograms. Most of the lettuce is sold to Hunan, Sichuan, and
Shaanxi provinces and brings in about 3,500 yuan (420
U.S. dollars) per mu.
</P>
<P>
By 2000, there are plans to plant 20,000 mu of lettuce and
garlic, and by 2010, to expand that to 80,000 mu, making the
province a leading lettuce and garlic producer for the
country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
