<HEADLINE> First International Air Route for Eastern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Regular air cargo service
between Winnipeg in Canada and Lukou Airport in Nanjing, capital
of Jiangsu Province, is now available every Monday, Thursday and
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first international air route of this eastern
Chinese province. There will be three return flights, with one
single trip via Sapporo of Japan taking 20 hours.
</P>
<P>
Previously, cargo for North America from Jiangsu and Shanghai
could only be carried by sea, often taking more than a month.
</P>
<P>
The air cargo service was started November 2 by Kelowna, a
Canadian air cargo company.
</P>
<P>
A new service between the airport and that in Amsterdam, the
Netherlands, is expected to start later this year, airport
authorities said, adding that discussions are underway for
operating flights to Japan, Malaysia, the Republic of Korea, and
Russia.
</P>
<P>
Lukou Airport went into operation in July last year and has 58
routes to major Chinese cities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
