<HEADLINE> Panama Sends Over 10 Tons of Aid to Hurricane-Hit Honduras </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, November 10 (Xinhua) -- A plane carrying more than
10 tons of aid left Panama City on Tuesday for Honduras, which
suffered the worst of Hurricane Mitch when it struck Central
America.
</P>
<P>
The aid, including food, potable water, clothes, medicine and
rescue equipment, will be distributed to over two million people
who were left homeless after Mitch devastated the country,
destroying 70 percent of its crops.
</P>
<P>
More than 7,000 people were reportedly killed and 12,000 still
missing in Honduras two weeks after Mitch hit Central America,
where the total toll is estimated to be at least 11,000.
</P>
<P>
Panama has also sent two helicopters to Nicaragua to help
rescuers and distribute international aid to hurricane victims.
</P>
</TEXT>
