<HEADLINE> IDB Launches Global Bond Issue of $1 Bln </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 10 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) Tuesday launched a 1 billion U.S. dollar
global issue, the second of the current calendar year.
</P>
<P>
The bonds carry a semiannual coupon of 5.375 percent and mature
on November 18, 2008.
</P>
<P>
J.P. Morgan Securities and Morgan Stanley Dean Witter are the
joint lead managers of the issue, which was priced at a spread of
64 basis points over the 4.75 percent U.S. Treasury due November
2008, giving a re-offer price of 99.504 percent.
</P>
<P>
The proceeds of the issue will be used to help finance the
social and economic development in Latin America and the Caribbean
region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
