<HEADLINE> World Bank Okays Two Large Loans for Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 10 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Tuesday
approved two large loans totaling some 3.03 billion U.S. dollars
for Argentina.
</P>
<P>
First loan of 2.52525 billion dollars is provided as a Special
Structural Adjustment Loan. This project will support the
continued efforts of the Government of Argentina to transform its
economy and to protect the gains achieved so far.
</P>
<P>
This project's operations are preventative, aimed at mitigating
the deleterious effect of the current international financial
instability on the economy and protecting vulnerable groups. This
project will also help meet critical foreign exchange needs of the
Government and will allow it to remain focused on longer term
reform issues.
</P>
<P>
Another loan of 505.05 million dollars is earmarked as Special
Repurchase Facility Support Loan.
</P>
<P>
This project, in conjunction with the Special Structural
Adjustment Loan above, will strengthen the country's financial
system's safety net and will safeguard economic and social
achievements.  
</P>
</TEXT>
