<HEADLINE> U.S. Women Love to Play Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 10 (Xinhua) -- More than ever, it's
female hands dribbling basketball on America's gym floors,
playgrounds and driveways.
</P>
<P>
Between 1987 and 1997, the number of women who played
basketball increased 25%, from 11 million to 13.7 million,
according to annual national surveys that track participation in
some 60 sports, fitness and outdoor activities.
</P>
<P>
More women play basketball than play any other team sport.
"When we look at the most committed players, we see that the
female population is growing more rapidly," said Gregg Hartley,
executive director of the American Basketball Council. 
</P>
