<HEADLINE> Jiangsu's Township Enterprises Grow Steadily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Rural and township enterprises
in east China's Jiangsu Province have developed steadily this
year, official figures indicate.
</P>
<P>
The incremental value of these enterprises in Jiangsu surged
15.1 percent on a yearly basis in the first nine months this year,
with growth rates for sales revenue and gross profits even higher.
</P>
<P>
Officials attributed this rapid growth to the fast expansion of
joint-stock and private companies.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu is one of China's economic powerhouses and a vanguard
of the country's market reforms. Its rural and township
enterprises, especially those in the southern region, are among
the most developed in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
