<HEADLINE> University Enrolment Hits New High in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, November 10 (Xinhua) -- The number of full-time
university students hit a new high of 507,195 this fall in Canada,
say preliminary figures from Statistics Canada Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Over the last five years, enrolment has fluctuated between
500,000 and 504,000. This year's registration has increased by
5,791 students or 1.2 per cent over last fall.
</P>
<P>
For the sixth straight year, the number of part-time students
dropped to 200,050 from 206,435 last year. That's a decrease of
2.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Among the provinces, British Columbia showed a 14.7-per-cent
increase in registrations. The number of students enrolled in
Alberta rose 4.8 per cent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
